 BRIEF0 {
  coords 4509.975 19.345 1476.094
  m_sTitle "TIME, WEATHER & TERRAIN"
  m_sTextData "a. Time & Weather"\
  "Time:  02:40"\
  "Sunrise: 02:29 "\
  "Sunset: 16:44"\
  "Weather: Good Visibility, Clear Day, No Recent Precipitation or Expected"\
  ""\
  "b. Terrain"\
  "Obstacles: ENY has deployed canalizing minefields west and east of the objective. South of OBJ Hill an obstacle has been deployed formed by 3 rows of triple concertina wire. The obstacle is 10 meters in depth with accompanied AP/AT mines."\
  ""\
  "Avenues of Approach:  Primary avenue of approach is from the south in order to avoid ENY western and eastern mienfields. The approach has undulating terrain providing pockets of dead ground. "\
  ""\
  "Key Terrain: Hill 35 occupied by ENY is decisive terrain as its control is vital to missions success. A small hill (0391 0131) to the southeast provides good overwatch for any COY manuvers east of that position."\
  ""\
  "Field of Observation: The ENY has almost unobstructed sightlines up to DT Romeo West of TRP1. The ENY's observation is blocked to the North East by uncontinous and sporadic sparse treelines, estimated visiibility to the North East is 600m from the ENY position. COY can travel unobserved up to the PLD (purple PL)."\
  ""\
  "Cover and Concealment: Smalls shrubs will provide concealment and undulating terrain throughout the AO will provide sporadic cover."\
  ""\
  " "
  m_aVisibleForFactions {
   "US"
  }
 }
}